The paper deals with optimization problems related to coded caching, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves decentralized algorithms (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI). The optimization problems are nonconvex and require techniques for solving Complementary Geometric Programming (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents information-theoretic converse bounds, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
